  "prompt": "How can I find out when an Instagram was created?",
  "response": "Here are a few ways to find out when an Instagram account was created:\n\n1. On the Instagram App/Website:\n- Go to the user's profile\n- Scroll down and look at their first post (which will be closest to the account's creation date)\n- Check the date of their earliest post\n\n2. Third-Party Websites:\n- Some websites like \"HypeAuditor\" or \"Social Blade\" can provide account creation dates\n- Many require free or paid registration\n\n3. Manual Method:\n- If the account has been active for a while, scroll through their very first posts\n- The date of their earliest post will give you a good indication of when the account started\n\n4. For Your Own Account:\n- Go to Settings > Account > Your Activity > Account History\n- This will show your account creation date\n\n5. Technical Note:\n- There's no direct \"official\" way to see the exact creation date within Instagram itself\n- The first post or earliest post chronologically is usually the best indicator\n\nRemember that these methods provide an approximate date, not always the precise creation moment.",
